WEBVTT

00:00.051 --> 00:01.780
Can I just say that
you're choosing to date

00:01.810 --> 00:02.598
a football player?

00:02.608 --> 00:04.582
He doesn't buy
into the whole jock thing.

00:04.746 --> 00:05.933
People change.

00:05.934 --> 00:07.447
Especially when they're
on the team.

00:08.183 --> 00:09.922
Look, it's just some
pick-me-ups I've been taking.

00:10.169 --> 00:11.406
What are you doing
to my son?

00:11.407 --> 00:12.757
I don't know
what's going on here.

00:12.758 --> 00:13.616
This!

00:13.616 --> 00:16.070
Smash is not gonna be
playing the game Friday night.

00:16.103 --> 00:17.589
What?

00:17.700 --> 00:18.510
Am I off the team?

00:18.514 --> 00:20.188
I should have reported this.

00:20.189 --> 00:21.771
You're gonna get yourself clean.

00:21.907 --> 00:23.461
Dad's down
in Corpus Christi.

00:23.468 --> 00:24.720
He's working on a driving range.

00:24.747 --> 00:26.130
Couple of postcards
every year

00:26.138 --> 00:27.610
and he gets off scot-free!

00:27.617 --> 00:29.002
I'm the one paying the bills
around here,

00:29.018 --> 00:30.951
going out there and watching
your damn football games.

00:30.956 --> 00:31.732
What's this?

00:31.736 --> 00:32.792
You've been served.

00:32.945 --> 00:33.691
Served by who?

00:33.738 --> 00:35.031
Jason Street's family.

00:35.488 --> 00:37.182
It's killing me to have
to do this to coach.

00:37.245 --> 00:38.912
The lawyers, my parents,
maybe they're right.

00:38.918 --> 00:41.210
Maybe if somebody teaches me
how to tackle somebody,

00:41.218 --> 00:42.272
I'm not in a chair.

00:42.318 --> 00:44.250
Why'd you set Lyla up
on a date with Ty Johnston?

00:44.348 --> 00:45.842
I don't want Lyla to be

00:45.848 --> 00:47.920
a caregiver her whole life, son.

00:47.938 --> 00:49.480
These Buddy Garritys of this world,

00:49.496 --> 00:51.143
they're a cancer to you and me.

00:51.147 --> 00:52.160
Lyla Garrity...

00:53.168 --> 00:54.370
will you marry me?

00:57.998 --> 00:59.133
So

00:59.155 --> 01:00.882
there's two cones
on either side of the goal.

01:00.915 --> 01:02.391
There's two goals, one
on either side of the court.

01:02.865 --> 01:04.052
You play on a basketball court.

01:04.328 --> 01:06.513
And the goal is
to get this ball--

01:06.566 --> 01:07.651
Y'all, watch those windows.

01:07.677 --> 01:08.970
And you wheel yourself through
the finish--

01:09.006 --> 01:09.630
That's okay.

01:09.708 --> 01:11.621
You wheel yourself through the goal line
and that's how you score.

01:12.807 --> 01:13.962
The position I really wanted

01:13.967 --> 01:16.190
- is called the "picker."
- It's like the quarterback, right?

01:16.248 --> 01:17.133
Right, right.

01:17.178 --> 01:18.553
He kinda controls the flow
of the game

01:18.587 --> 01:20.661
and he leads the breaks
and everything.

01:21.026 --> 01:22.130
You gotta be really fast.

01:22.157 --> 01:23.560
It's a really, really
hard position but

01:23.678 --> 01:25.263
I think-- I think
I'm good enough for it.

01:25.438 --> 01:27.993
So is this what I see them
playing at the YMCA sometimes?

01:28.036 --> 01:30.760
Oh, no, ma'am,
that's wheelchair basketball.

01:31.468 --> 01:32.800
Oh.There's a huge difference.

01:32.815 --> 01:34.363
Oh, yeah. Huge.

01:36.466 --> 01:38.442
Well, there is
a big difference, Mr. Garrity.

01:38.668 --> 01:40.642
The guys who play quad rugby,
they're world-class athletes.

01:40.706 --> 01:42.373
Three of them won medals last
year at the world championship.

01:42.376 --> 01:43.613
- Did they?
- Yeah.

01:44.007 --> 01:46.461
I know, it's great.
It's a great hobby.

01:46.867 --> 01:48.513
Come on, Dad, it's not a hobby.

01:48.577 --> 01:50.013
You can't make a living from it,
honey, so

01:50.097 --> 01:51.183
it must be a hobby.

01:53.107 --> 01:54.950
You guys, let's come on in
and eat, all right?

01:57.476 --> 01:58.672
You know what, Mr. Garrity?

01:58.728 --> 02:00.592
What exactly do you have
against quad rugby again?

02:00.657 --> 02:01.433
Nothing.

02:01.488 --> 02:02.771
Yes, you do 'cause
every time I come over here,

02:02.816 --> 02:04.280
- you're always making fun of it.
-Sweetie.

02:04.358 --> 02:06.593
All  I'm saying is it's not
a way to make a living.

02:07.645 --> 02:09.410
So what are you
gonna live off of, huh?

02:10.247 --> 02:12.390
- Lawsuit?
- Buddy, enough, okay?

02:12.436 --> 02:14.533
Oh, is that what this is about, Mr. Garrity?
You still pissed off about the lawsuits?

02:14.535 --> 02:15.811
- Yes, I am.
- What, are you a little kid?

02:15.815 --> 02:16.500
Get over it!

02:16.558 --> 02:18.033
Hey, let me tell
you something, son.

02:18.618 --> 02:20.421
You're suing my team.
You're suing my coach.

02:20.467 --> 02:22.561
- How do you expect me to feel?
- It's your team?

02:22.656 --> 02:24.302
How about a little compassion,
Mr. Garrity?

02:24.386 --> 02:26.063
I mean, I am paralyzed now.

02:26.075 --> 02:27.542
- Jason.
- All right, play the game.

02:27.635 --> 02:28.883
- Ply the gasme.
- I don't care. Play the game.

02:28.907 --> 02:30.193
I will play the game,
Mr. Garrity.

02:30.196 --> 02:31.130
- I will, I will.
- Do it.

02:31.135 --> 02:32.181
And when I make
the national team

02:32.198 --> 02:33.383
and I start touring
all over the world,

02:33.385 --> 02:34.421
I'll take your daughter
with me.

02:34.548 --> 02:35.560
How 'bout that?

02:35.727 --> 02:37.280
'Cause we're getting married.

02:38.686 --> 02:40.090
Excuse me?

02:41.106 --> 02:42.650
- That's right.
- Married?

02:42.765 --> 02:44.251
Yeah, we picked out a ring
this morning, didn't we?

02:48.377 --> 02:49.302
Okay.

02:54.076 --> 02:55.270
Daddy, please.

03:01.225 --> 03:02.441
What are you doing?

03:02.455 --> 03:03.830
What am I doing?
He's pushing me.

03:04.087 --> 03:05.121
- Jason.
- Hey.

03:05.367 --> 03:07.372
I'm not doing
anything wrong here, Lyla!

03:08.668 --> 03:09.443
Lyla!

